description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from enthusiastic and suitably qualified individuals for the post of Specialist Biomedical Scientist within the Department of Pathology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a HCPC registered Specialist Biomedical Scientist or equivalent. Experience of working with molecular techniques/methods and or in a Clinical Microbiology Department would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, friendly and well-motivated individual who is a good team player to support the newly formed covid testing laboratory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is currently based at the Queen’s Medical Centre Campus which is part of Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Vacancies are fixed term or secondment contracts for 6 months in the first instance with a view for extension. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working hours: Sunday-Sunday 37.5 hours per week &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stephanie Szolin - Pathology Care Group General manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07812 268765&lt;/p&gt;
